  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you\u2019ve forgotten your password for the SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) portal, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n### 1. **Visit the Official SSC Website**  \n   Go to the official SSC website: [https://ssc.nic.in](https://ssc.nic.in).\n\n### 2. **Click on \"Forgot Password\"**  \n   On the login page, look for the **\"Forgot Password\"** link and click on it.\n\n### 3. **Enter Required Details**  \n   You will be prompted to enter the following details:  \n   - **Registration Number**  \n   - **Date of Birth**  \n   - **Captcha Code**  \n\n### 4. **Submit and Verify**  \n   After entering the details, click on the **\"Submit\"** button.  \n\n### 5. **Reset Your Password**  \n   You will receive a link or OTP (One-Time Password) on your **registered email ID** or **mobile number** to reset your password. Follow the instructions provided in the email or SMS to create a new password.\n\n### 6. **Login with New Password**  \n   Once your password has been reset, log in to the SSC CGL portal using your **Registration Number** and the **new password**.\n\n### Additional Tips:  \n- Ensure that the email ID and mobile number you provided during registration are active and accessible.  \n- If you do not receive the reset link or OTP, check your **Spam/Junk** folder or re-initiate the process.  \n- If you continue to face issues, contact the SSC Helpdesk or Regional Office for assistance.  \n\n### SSC Helpdesk:  \n- **Email:** helpdesk@ssc.nic.in  \n- **Phone:** 011-69999845 (Monday to Friday, 10 AM to 5 PM)  \n\nMake sure to keep your new password secure and note it down for future reference.",
